    "abstract": "Sleep is an essential state of decreased activity and alertness but molecular factors regulating sleep duration remain unknown. Through genome-wide association analysis in 446,118 adults of European ancestry from the UK Biobank, we identify 78 loci for self-reported habitual sleep duration (p\u2009<\u20095\u2009\u00d7\u200910-8; 43 loci at p\u2009<\u20096\u2009\u00d7\u200910-9). Replication is observed for PAX8, VRK2, and FBXL12/UBL5/PIN1 loci in the CHARGE study (n\u2009=\u200947,180; p\u2009<\u20096.3\u2009\u00d7\u200910-4), and 55 signals show sign-concordant effects. The 78 "
